ch.dieseite.colladaloader.coreproc

Class SaxParser.Context<CI,RI>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.dieseite.colladaloader.coreproc.SaxParser.Context<CI,RI>
  • Enclosing class:
    SaxParser<CI,RI>

    public static class SaxParser.Context<CI,RI>
extends java.lang.Object

    A helper class

  • a) to cache callbacks from SaxParser
  • b) to define a certain tag in a certain xml tree to be found and
  • c) additional infos what to do next with that Record

      • isMatch

        private boolean isMatch()
        says if this level can be parsed Important; this method works only if inc/dec/updateHistory() is done before correctly i.e. oneOrMore: ( 1. inc(), 2. [dec()] update() ) Because size of history cache, the xml depth is limited to Long.BYTES*8 (=64)

      • updateHistory

        private void updateHistory(java.lang.String tagName,
                           org.xml.sax.Attributes attributes)
        check if current depth is a possible fetch tree. It sets true/false to the current focused history stack The history keeps true if the whole walkthrough until target xml leaf tag is match
        Parameters:
        currentDepth -
        tagName - can be a "name" or fine search "name#attribName=value" this can help to distinguish same tags using their attributes
        tagAttributes -
